SIMPLE: moke
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moke
<hw>Moke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stupid
person; a dolt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A donkey.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A negro.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Theat. Slang)</fld> <ety>[More fully <ets>musical
moke</ets>.]</ety> <def>A performer, as a minstrel, who plays on several
instruments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moke
<hw>Moke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mesh of a net, or of
anything resembling a net.</def> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moky</ent>⟦br⟧
